Chlorophyll Fluorescence

Light energy absorbed by a leaf can undergo one of three fates: it can be used to drive photosynthesis, dissipated as heat, or re-emitted as light chlorophyll fluorescence. We measure chlorophyll fluorescence as a ratio Fv/Fm. We can use this measurement to investigate how stressors damage the photosynthetic apparatus.

Lets look at a couple of plots

We can see the Tcrit for 11 species of trees found on the farm along with the all time record high temperature for Clarksville (red line), the hottest temperature for the respective month (orange line), and the highest temperature observed during the collection month (blue line).
